  <name>Dumber</name>
  <summary>A minimal keyboard-driven browser for tiling WMs</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      A dumb browser that works like your favorite terminal multiplexer.
      Wayland native, keyboard-driven with Zellij-inspired workflow, featuring
      tabs with split and stacked panes, built-in ad blocking, and session management.
    </p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Wayland native - no X11/XWayland dependency</li>
      <li>Tabs and workspaces with split or stacked panes</li>
      <li>Keyboard-driven workflow inspired by Zellij</li>
      <li>Smart popup handling for OAuth flows and tiling WMs</li>
      <li>GPU rendering with automatic VA-API/VDPAU detection</li>
      <li>Built-in ad blocking with UBlock-based filtering</li>
      <li>Launcher integration with rofi/fuzzel support</li>
      <li>Search shortcuts via bangs</li>
      <li>Customizable light and dark themes</li>
      <li>Session save/restore with automatic snapshots</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
